f the C library 'Google CRC32C'\"\n   readme = \"README.md\"\n   requires-python = \">=3.9\"\n   license = {text = \"Apache-2.0\"}\n   authors = [\n     {name = \"Google LLC\", email = \"googleapis-packages@google.com\"}\n   ]\n   classifiers = [\n     \"Development Status :: 4 - Beta\",\n     \"Intended Audience :: Developers\",\n     \"Operating System :: OS Independent\",\n     \"Programming Language :: Python :: 3\",\n     \"Programming Language :: Python :: 3.9\",\n     \"Programming Language :: Python :: 3.10\",\n     \"Programming Language :: Python :: 3.11\",\n     \"Programming Language :: Python :: 3.12\",\n     \"Programming Language :: Python :: 3.13\"\n   ]\n   dependencies = [\n     'importlib_resources>=1.3; python_version < \"3.9\" and os_name == \"nt\"'\n   ]\n   \n   [project.optional-dependencies]\n   testing = [\"pytest\"]\n   ```\n3. **Option C (Add dynamic fields)**: Keep minimal `pyproject.toml` but add `dynamic` field:\n   ```toml\n   [build-system]\n   requires = [\"setuptools\", \"wheel\"]\n   \n   [project]\n   dynamic = [\"version\", \"license\", \"authors\", \"classifiers\", \"dependencies\", \"optional-dependencies\"]\n   ```\n\n**Recommended Approach**:\n**Option A (Remove pyproject.toml)** is recommended because:\n1. It's the simplest and most reliable fix\n2. The project already has complete configuration in `setup.cfg`\n3. It avoids complex PEP 621 conversion\n4. It matches the project's current setup.py which reads from setup.cfg\n\n**Implementation Steps**:\n1. Delete `/root/fix_build_agent/process/project/g-py-crc32c/pyproject.toml`\n2. Verify `setup.cfg` has all necessary configuration (it does)\n3. The build should then use only `setup.cfg` without PEP 621 validation conflicts\n\n**Key Insight from Previous Attempts**:\n- Attempt 4 showed that setuptools reads license from setup.cfg as string, not from pyproject.toml as dictionary\n- The real problem is conflicting definitions between setup.cfg and pyproject.toml\n- When migrating from setup.cfg to pyproject.toml, ensure no conflicting definitions exist\n- Setuptools may read from both files, causing ambiguity\n\n**Files to Examine**:\n1. `/root/fix_build_agent/process/project/g-py-crc32c/pyproject.toml` - Current minimal file causing the issue\n2. `/root/fix_build_agent/process/project/g-py-crc32c/setup.cfg` - Complete configuration\n3. `/root/fix_build_agent/process/project/g-py-crc32c/setup.py` - Build script that uses setup.cfg"})
