.cfg and pyproject.toml\n- When migrating from setup.cfg to pyproject.toml, ensure no conflicting definitions exist\n- Setuptools may read from both files, causing ambiguity\n\n**Files to Examine**:\n1. `/root/fix_build_agent/process/project/g-py-crc32c/pyproject.toml` - Current minimal file causing the issue\n2. `/root/fix_build_agent/process/project/g-py-crc32c/setup.cfg` - Complete configuration\n3. `/root/fix_build_agent/process/project/g-py-crc32c/setup.py` - Build script that uses setup.cfg\n\n--- 【LESSONS FROM PREVIOUS ATTEMPTS】 ---\n- [Attempt 4] Stagnant: Same error as Attempt 3. The issue is that setuptools is reading license from setup.cfg (\'Apache 2.0\' as string) not from pyproject.toml ({text = \'Apache-2.0\'} as dictionary). The dynamic field approach isn\'t working - setuptools still reads from setup.cfg and tries to access val[\'text\'] on a string, causing KeyError. The real problem is conflicting definitions between setup.cfg and pyproject.toml. Lesson: When migrating from setup.cfg to pyproject.toml, ensure no conflicting definitions exist. Setuptools may read from both files, causing ambiguity. Need to either remove conflicting definitions from setup.cfg or ensure pyproject.toml takes precedence.\n- [Attempt 1] The Dockerfile patching introduced a syntax error: added \'-python\' suffix after the digest, which is invalid Docker image reference format. Docker digests must be at the end of the reference. The original error was a Python packaging configuration issue (pyproject.toml license field), but now we can\'t even start the build due to Docker syntax error.\n- [Attempt 2] Docker build succeeded after fixing syntax error. The C library compilation also succeeded. The error is now in Python packaging: setuptools expects license to be a dictionary with \'text\' key (per pyproject.toml schema) but reads \'Apache 2.0\' as a string from setup.cfg. Removing \'license_files\' resolved the file/text conflict, but now setuptools is trying to validate setup.cfg configuration against pyproject.toml schema. The minimal pyproject.toml with only [build-system] causes setuptools to expect PEP 621 compliance for all metadata. Need to either: 1) Add proper [project] table to pyproject.toml with license = {text = \'Apache-2.0\'}, 2) Add dynamic fields to pyproject.toml, or 3) Remove pyproject.toml entirely to force setuptools to use only setup.cfg.\n\n\n--- Configuration Files (Dockerfile, build.sh, etc.) ---\n\n### Content from: Dockerfile ###\n# Copyright 2022 Google LLC\n#\n# Licensed under the Apache License, Version 2.0 (the "License");\n# you may not use this file except in compliance with the License.\n# You may obtain a copy of the License at\n#\n#      http://www.apache.org/licenses/LICENSE-2.0\n#\n# Unless required by applicable law or agreed to in writing, software\n# distributed under the License is distributed on an "AS IS" BASIS,\n# WITHOUT WARRANTIES OR CONDITIONS OF ANY KIND, either express or implied.\n# See the License for the specific language governing permissions and\n# limitations under the License.\n#\n################################################################################\n\nFROM gcr.io/oss-fuzz-base/base-builder-python@sha256:5a22963e0582b5ce74e3dac5c175a321dc0cbe319c2851c370b885588327a055\nRUN git clone https://github.com/googleapis/python-crc32c\nCOPY build.sh *.py $SRC/\nWORKDIR python-crc32c\n\n### Content from: build.sh ###\n#!/bin/bash -eu\n# Copyright 2022 Google LLC\n#\n# Licensed under the Apache License, Version 2.0 (the "License");\n# you may not use this file except in compliance with the License.\n# You may obtain a copy of the License at\n#\n#      http://www.apache.org/licenses/LICENSE-2.0\n#\n# Unless required by applicable law or agreed to in writing, software\n# distributed under the License is distributed on an "AS IS" BASIS,\n# WITHOUT WARRANTIES OR CONDITIONS OF ANY KIND, either express or implied.\n# See the License for the specific language governing permissions and\n# limitations under the License.\n#\n################################################################################\n\ngit submodule update --init --recursive\n\nmkdir usr\nexport CRC32C_INSTALL_PREFIX=$(pwd)/usr\n\nmkdir google_crc32c/build\ncd google_crc32c/build\ncmake \\\n  -DCMAKE_BUILD_TYPE=Release \\\n  -DCRC32C_BUILD_TESTS=no \\\n  -DCRC32C_BUILD_BENCHMARKS=no \\\n  -DBUILD_SHARED_LIBS=yes \\\n  -DCMAKE_INSTALL_PREFIX:PATH=${CRC32C_INSTALL_PREFIX} \\\n  ../\nmake all install\ncd ../../\n\n\npython3 setup.py build_ext \\\n  --include-dirs=$(pwd)/usr/include \\\n  --library-dirs=$(pwd)/usr/lib \\\n  --rpath=$(pwd)/usr/lib\npip3 install -e .[testing]\n\n# Build fuzzers in $OUT.\nfor fuzzer in $(find $SRC -name \'fuzz_*.py\'); do\n  compile_python_fuzzer $fuzzer\ndone\n\n### Content from: fuzz_checksum.py ###\n#!/usr/bin/python3\n# Copyright 2022 Google LLC\n#\n# Licensed under the Apache License, Version 2.0 (the "License");\n# you may not use this file except in compliance with the License.\n# You may obtain a copy of the License at\n#\n#      http://www.apache.org/licenses/LICENSE-2.0\n#\n# Unless required by applicable law or agreed to in writing, software\n# distributed under the License is distributed on an "AS IS" BASIS,\n# WITHOUT WARRANTIES OR CONDITIONS OF ANY KIND, either express or implied.\n# See the License for the specific language governing permissions and\n# limitations under the License.\n\nimport atheris\nimport sys\n\nwith atheris.instrument_imports():\n  import google_crc32c\n\ndef TestOneInput(data):\n  val1 = google_crc32c.value(data)\n  val2 = google_crc32c.Checksum(data)._crc\n  assert val1 == val2\n\n\ndef main():\n  atheris.Setup(sys.argv, TestOneInput, enable_python_coverage=True)\n  atheris.Fuzz()\n\nif __name__ == "__main__":\n  main()\n\n### Content from: project.yaml ###\nfuzzing_engines:\n- libfuzzer\nhomepage: https://github.com/googleapis/python-crc32c\nlanguage: python\nmain_repo: https://github.com/googleapis/python-crc32